Syntax highlighting of published code makes for much <span style="text-decoration:line-through;">prettier</span> more legible code.

I experimented with several of the more common pastebin-like services: with [Github's gist service](http://gist.github.com/), and with the original [Pastebin.com](http://pastebin.com/) service.

Here's an example from [pastebin](http://pastebin.com/):

![7171659687_56db0dda3f](http://ootput.files.wordpress.com/2010/04/7171659687_56db0dda3f.jpg)

Compare that to [Github's gists](https://gist.github.com/):

![7171659637_1103fd5416](http://ootput.files.wordpress.com/2010/04/7171659637_1103fd5416.jpg)

Gists also have line numbers, but they're only visible when viewed directly, e.g. [here](http://gist.github.com/358730#file_gistfile1.html)